1
00:01:00,945 --> 00:01:03,065
I'm glad to see you again.

2
00:01:03,145 --> 00:01:05,545
Maylin is the daughter
of one of my mom's close friends.

3
00:01:05,624 --> 00:01:08,105
Your mom seems to hope for more.

4
00:01:08,185 --> 00:01:10,025
Can I ask you something?

5
00:01:10,105 --> 00:01:11,945
You have a crush on Runch, right?

6
00:01:12,025 --> 00:01:13,225
Aunt Ging!

7
00:01:13,305 --> 00:01:15,345
Let's just keep hugging.
It warms my heart.

8
00:01:16,345 --> 00:01:18,305
I hope your plan will succeed.

9
00:01:18,905 --> 00:01:20,065
An actual shooting star--

10
00:01:32,945 --> 00:01:34,785
What are you looking at, Runch?

11
00:01:36,705 --> 00:01:40,105
I'm looking to confirm this isn't a dream.

12
00:01:43,065 --> 00:01:45,705
Waking up to see your face

13
00:01:46,545 --> 00:01:48,185
just makes me so happy.

14
00:01:52,145 --> 00:01:55,545
Isn't it a bit too early for that?
You're making me blush.

15
00:02:02,825 --> 00:02:05,265
You were blushing last night too.

16
00:02:06,345 --> 00:02:08,864
And also the other night.

17
00:02:09,744 --> 00:02:11,345
And the night before that.

18
00:02:11,425 --> 00:02:14,065
Stop it.

19
00:02:16,305 --> 00:02:18,585
If you go sleep anywhere else,

20
00:02:18,665 --> 00:02:20,305
I won't allow it.

21
00:02:22,105 --> 00:02:24,465
I don't want to go anywhere either.

22
00:02:24,985 --> 00:02:27,985
I just want to lie next to you like this.

23
00:02:31,025 --> 00:02:32,625
Gorgeous.

24
00:02:35,625 --> 00:02:38,265
I like the nicknames you give me.

25
00:02:38,905 --> 00:02:40,225
Like what?

26
00:02:41,545 --> 00:02:43,665
Like…

27
00:02:45,745 --> 00:02:47,265
"my girl,"

28
00:02:47,785 --> 00:02:50,145
"my wife,"

29
00:02:50,225 --> 00:02:52,465
or "mine."

30
00:02:55,345 --> 00:02:57,585
I'm so happy to hear that.

31
00:02:59,585 --> 00:03:01,705
My girl.

32
00:03:02,705 --> 00:03:05,345
My wife.

33
00:03:07,945 --> 00:03:10,265
You're mine.

34
00:03:13,265 --> 00:03:14,265
Then…

35
00:03:21,145 --> 00:03:23,585
can I be yours forever?

36
00:03:26,385 --> 00:03:29,145
I'd never let anyone else have you.

37
00:04:29,265 --> 00:04:30,825
Yes, Mr. Apichet?

38
00:04:33,505 --> 00:04:34,465
Sure.

39
00:04:47,305 --> 00:04:50,505
-Mrs. Runch, please have a seat.
-Sure.

40
00:04:57,385 --> 00:04:59,665
-Maylin!
-Runch.

41
00:05:00,785 --> 00:05:02,705
So you know each other?

42
00:05:02,785 --> 00:05:05,305
Yes, we do.

43
00:05:05,385 --> 00:05:06,385
Perfect, then.

44
00:05:06,465 --> 00:05:09,705
Maylin's advisor
is a close friend of mine,

45
00:05:09,785 --> 00:05:13,305
so she asked me to hire
one of her best students.

46
00:05:13,385 --> 00:05:16,345
I saw that your team still needed people,

47
00:05:16,425 --> 00:05:20,305
so I decided to hire her
to work on your team.

48
00:05:20,385 --> 00:05:24,665
Sure. I'll take care of Maylin
as best I can.

49
00:05:25,385 --> 00:05:27,065
Thank you, Runch.

50
00:05:27,145 --> 00:05:29,745
I've wanted to work with you for so long.

51
00:05:31,545 --> 00:05:34,585
Could you train her right away?

52
00:05:34,665 --> 00:05:35,825
Sure.

53
00:05:43,945 --> 00:05:45,505
-This is it.
-Okay.

54
00:05:52,825 --> 00:05:53,985
Everyone,

55
00:05:55,425 --> 00:05:59,225
this is Maylin. She's new here.
Please take good care of her.

56
00:06:00,665 --> 00:06:03,065
Hello. My name is Maylin.

57
00:06:03,145 --> 00:06:05,065
I'm looking forward to working with you.

58
00:06:07,865 --> 00:06:08,785
This way.

59
00:06:16,265 --> 00:06:17,705
This is your desk.

60
00:06:17,785 --> 00:06:20,305
If there's anything you want to know
or don't understand,

61
00:06:20,385 --> 00:06:22,425
feel free to ask me. Don't be shy.

62
00:06:22,505 --> 00:06:23,945
Sure, Runch.

63
00:06:24,585 --> 00:06:26,345
I'll bring the documents

64
00:06:26,425 --> 00:06:29,785
on our current case
for you to read for now.

65
00:06:29,865 --> 00:06:31,385
Sure.

66
00:06:31,465 --> 00:06:33,345
-Make yourself at home.
-Thank you.

67
00:06:42,305 --> 00:06:46,025
Welcome, Maylin. My name is Utt.

68
00:06:47,705 --> 00:06:49,705
Hello. I'm Maylin.

69
00:06:52,305 --> 00:06:55,625
So you and Runch already know each other?

70
00:06:56,425 --> 00:06:59,025
Yes, we've known each other
for a while now.

71
00:07:00,065 --> 00:07:01,065
Since we were little.

72
00:07:53,385 --> 00:07:54,425
Neen.

73
00:07:57,505 --> 00:07:59,305
Home already?

74
00:08:00,425 --> 00:08:03,785
I arranged a little something for you.

75
00:08:09,265 --> 00:08:11,145
You did this for me?

76
00:08:11,225 --> 00:08:14,385
Yeah. I saw that
you always came home tired,

77
00:08:14,465 --> 00:08:17,065
so I wanted to help you take the edge off.

78
00:08:17,985 --> 00:08:20,905
If you don't find it pretty,
or if you don't like it,

79
00:08:20,985 --> 00:08:22,305
please forgive me.

80
00:08:23,585 --> 00:08:25,385
It's beautiful.

81
00:08:26,545 --> 00:08:30,385
No matter what you do for me,
I'll always like it.

82
00:08:55,025 --> 00:08:56,945
There's one more thing
I want to ask of you.

83
00:08:58,185 --> 00:08:59,425
What is it?

84
00:09:05,985 --> 00:09:07,865
I bought an outfit.

85
00:09:08,625 --> 00:09:10,905
I wanted to wear it for you tonight.

86
00:09:12,385 --> 00:09:16,385
But it'd look much better
if you put it on me.

87
00:09:18,705 --> 00:09:20,065
Can you help me?

88
00:09:20,145 --> 00:09:21,665
Of course.

89
00:09:32,865 --> 00:09:34,465
But…

90
00:09:43,265 --> 00:09:44,545
I think

91
00:09:46,185 --> 00:09:50,305
you'd look better with no clothes on.

92
00:10:23,105 --> 00:10:26,825
Intent is the key issue in this case,

93
00:10:27,345 --> 00:10:30,465
so you have to go through
the timeline in each slot.

94
00:10:31,905 --> 00:10:33,185
Got it, Runch.

95
00:10:36,785 --> 00:10:38,265
Also,

96
00:10:39,265 --> 00:10:42,185
try opening that file.

97
00:10:44,225 --> 00:10:45,385
This one?

98
00:11:00,185 --> 00:11:03,145
See? It's just like I said.

99
00:11:03,785 --> 00:11:06,345
There's something going on
between those two.

100
00:11:07,145 --> 00:11:09,945
Why'd they have to be so close
just to look at some documents?

101
00:11:11,105 --> 00:11:12,345
This can't be normal.

102
00:11:12,425 --> 00:11:14,025
Yeah, it's obvious.

103
00:11:14,105 --> 00:11:16,465
The new girl seems
totally in love with our boss.

104
00:11:16,545 --> 00:11:19,905
Runch is so hot.
Of course the new girl would fall for her.

105
00:11:21,065 --> 00:11:22,585
Trust me,

106
00:11:22,665 --> 00:11:25,625
there's something going on between them.

107
00:11:29,945 --> 00:11:32,705
Hey, give it back. I'll be right back.

108
00:11:32,785 --> 00:11:33,905
Ms. Neen.

109
00:11:34,825 --> 00:11:37,465
-Are you here to see our boss?
-Yes.

110
00:11:37,545 --> 00:11:40,425
Oh, didn't you call her before you came?

111
00:11:40,505 --> 00:11:42,985
She just went out with the new girl.

112
00:11:44,825 --> 00:11:47,305
-New girl?
-Yes.

113
00:11:47,905 --> 00:11:51,705
See… I don't know if I should say this,

114
00:11:51,785 --> 00:11:53,705
but I don't want you
to get the wrong idea later.

115
00:11:54,305 --> 00:11:55,985
Please say it. I'm all ears.

116
00:11:57,665 --> 00:12:01,745
Well… Lately, Runch and the new girl,

117
00:12:02,265 --> 00:12:05,385
Maylin, have been working together
on a project every day.

118
00:12:08,065 --> 00:12:10,665
Isn't it normal for them
to work together every day?

119
00:12:11,465 --> 00:12:12,905
Well, it is.

120
00:12:13,625 --> 00:12:17,345
But I think they seem

121
00:12:17,425 --> 00:12:19,385
awfully close.

122
00:12:20,385 --> 00:12:22,905
I hear they already knew each other,

123
00:12:22,985 --> 00:12:24,985
since they were little.

124
00:12:28,265 --> 00:12:30,385
I don't want you two to fight,

125
00:12:31,145 --> 00:12:35,345
but this photo is quite telling.

126
00:12:48,585 --> 00:12:51,425
I guess it's because of their new project.

127
00:12:51,945 --> 00:12:54,185
Runch has always been serious
about her work.

128
00:12:54,945 --> 00:12:57,905
Yes. I hope that's the case too.

129
00:12:59,185 --> 00:13:00,305
If you'll excuse me.

130
00:13:14,465 --> 00:13:15,905
<i>Lately, Runch</i>

131
00:13:15,985 --> 00:13:18,425
<i>and the new girl, Maylin, have been</i>

132
00:13:18,945 --> 00:13:20,505
<i>working together on a project every day.</i>

133
00:13:20,585 --> 00:13:24,505
They seem awfully close.

134
00:13:24,585 --> 00:13:27,265
This photo is quite telling.

135
00:13:39,385 --> 00:13:40,905
I'm sorry.

136
00:13:45,425 --> 00:13:47,145
Sorry for coming home late.

137
00:13:48,265 --> 00:13:50,305
My client just wouldn't stop talking.

138
00:13:51,945 --> 00:13:55,105
It's okay. You always work hard anyway.

139
00:13:57,145 --> 00:13:58,825
I've missed you all day.

140
00:14:04,505 --> 00:14:06,425
How's work going?

141
00:14:07,785 --> 00:14:11,905
I'm working on our case strategy.
There's quite a bit of work.

142
00:14:16,545 --> 00:14:19,105
You have so many new projects.

143
00:14:19,185 --> 00:14:21,345
Your team must be hiring
someone new, right?

144
00:14:22,705 --> 00:14:24,585
-There's a new girl.
-Yeah?

145
00:14:24,665 --> 00:14:26,585
But she's still new to the job.

146
00:14:26,665 --> 00:14:29,065
So I have to supervise her closely.

147
00:14:32,385 --> 00:14:34,705
Well, who's the new girl?

148
00:14:35,425 --> 00:14:37,385
Mr. Apichet hired her.

149
00:14:39,905 --> 00:14:42,505
Someone recommended her to him.

150
00:14:43,025 --> 00:14:46,465
Once the project settles down,
I'll be able to delegate more.

151
00:14:47,385 --> 00:14:49,665
But for now, we'll have to work together.

152
00:14:52,465 --> 00:14:56,385
Runch, are you close to her?

153
00:14:57,745 --> 00:14:58,745
No.

154
00:15:01,945 --> 00:15:03,625
She's just a coworker.

155
00:15:14,745 --> 00:15:17,585
<i>Lately, Runch and the new girl,</i>

156
00:15:18,105 --> 00:15:21,185
<i>Maylin, have been working together</i>
<i>on a project every day.</i>

157
00:15:21,265 --> 00:15:25,385
<i>They seem awfully close.</i>

158
00:15:26,625 --> 00:15:28,905
Why can't I stop thinking about it?

159
00:15:29,425 --> 00:15:30,665
Ms. Neen,

160
00:15:31,185 --> 00:15:32,465
is something wrong?

161
00:15:36,105 --> 00:15:40,345
Nothing. I just have something on my mind.

162
00:15:48,265 --> 00:15:49,185
Nat,

163
00:15:49,265 --> 00:15:51,585
I have something to take care of.
I won't be back.

164
00:15:51,665 --> 00:15:53,385
Call me if you need anything.

165
00:16:00,905 --> 00:16:02,145
Okay. That's all.

166
00:16:05,385 --> 00:16:07,265
Ms. Neen! Hello.

167
00:16:07,345 --> 00:16:08,545
Hello.

168
00:16:11,625 --> 00:16:12,905
Is Runch here?

169
00:16:16,865 --> 00:16:20,465
We need to go over
the witness's testimony again

170
00:16:20,545 --> 00:16:23,865
and compare it
with the opposing party's timeline.

171
00:16:23,945 --> 00:16:27,745
If we aren't accurate about this part,
I'm afraid they'll use it to press us.

172
00:16:33,025 --> 00:16:34,185
Maylin,

173
00:16:34,865 --> 00:16:36,185
are you okay?

174
00:16:39,465 --> 00:16:41,385
I'm okay.

175
00:16:41,465 --> 00:16:44,065
Just feeling a little dizzy.

176
00:16:45,345 --> 00:16:47,225
Did you get enough sleep last night?

177
00:16:48,225 --> 00:16:51,305
I only slept for two hours last night.

178
00:16:52,145 --> 00:16:54,985
I was busy preparing the summary for you.

179
00:16:55,585 --> 00:16:57,745
Two hours isn't nearly enough.

180
00:17:00,105 --> 00:17:03,425
When building cases,
your focus is important.

181
00:17:03,945 --> 00:17:07,265
If your body's weak,
then your brain is weak too.

182
00:17:09,625 --> 00:17:11,745
I just wanted to do my best.

183
00:17:12,545 --> 00:17:14,665
I didn't want to disappoint you.

184
00:17:15,704 --> 00:17:19,025
Why don't you leave and get some rest?
You may come back later.

185
00:17:20,265 --> 00:17:21,184
Sure.

186
00:17:28,265 --> 00:17:29,185
Maylin!

187
00:17:29,265 --> 00:17:30,185
Boss.

188
00:17:35,105 --> 00:17:36,465
Neen!

189
00:17:40,345 --> 00:17:41,745
I'm sorry, Boss.

190
00:17:41,825 --> 00:17:45,185
Ms. Neen asked to see you,
so I brought her.

191
00:17:45,265 --> 00:17:48,105
I didn't think you and Maylin would be…

192
00:17:50,665 --> 00:17:52,025
Neen.

193
00:17:58,905 --> 00:17:59,745
You should sit down.

194
00:18:01,145 --> 00:18:02,225
Sit down and rest.

195
00:18:03,985 --> 00:18:05,185
Neen!

196
00:18:12,105 --> 00:18:13,305
Mr. Utt,

197
00:18:14,505 --> 00:18:17,345
who's that woman?

198
00:18:20,465 --> 00:18:21,905
She's Runch's wife.

199
00:18:28,625 --> 00:18:30,345
Neen.

200
00:18:32,745 --> 00:18:35,865
Please let me explain.
It's not what you think.

201
00:18:40,705 --> 00:18:43,585
She was dizzy, and she almost fainted.

202
00:18:43,665 --> 00:18:45,865
So I grabbed her.

203
00:18:46,465 --> 00:18:48,265
That's all.

204
00:18:49,705 --> 00:18:51,345
I'll take your word for it.

205
00:18:51,985 --> 00:18:53,545
But there's one more thing.

206
00:18:54,185 --> 00:18:56,825
Utt said you've known her
since you were little.

207
00:18:57,465 --> 00:18:58,825
Is that true?

208
00:19:05,665 --> 00:19:07,945
I was afraid you'd feel uncomfortable.

209
00:19:08,465 --> 00:19:12,025
I didn't want you to worry,
so I didn't tell you.

210
00:19:18,945 --> 00:19:20,145
So you decided

211
00:19:20,225 --> 00:19:22,505
what to tell or not to tell.

212
00:19:22,585 --> 00:19:24,825
You decided without even asking me.

213
00:19:30,625 --> 00:19:32,465
I always trusted you.

214
00:19:34,185 --> 00:19:36,305
But today, you made me feel

215
00:19:36,985 --> 00:19:40,145
like you have a secret life
I don't know about.

216
00:19:41,265 --> 00:19:44,225
I'm afraid there's more
that I don't know about.

217
00:19:47,505 --> 00:19:49,705
Is there anything else
you haven't told me?

218
00:19:52,705 --> 00:19:55,585
No. There's absolutely nothing else.

219
00:19:56,385 --> 00:19:58,385
And I won't let it happen again.

220
00:19:59,065 --> 00:20:01,225
I won't hide anything from you ever again.

221
00:20:01,865 --> 00:20:03,065
I promise.

222
00:20:29,745 --> 00:20:31,585
Yes, Maylin?

223
00:20:32,465 --> 00:20:36,385
Are you free this evening?
Would you like to come over for dinner?

224
00:20:37,305 --> 00:20:39,665
Oh? You wanted to talk to me
about something too?

225
00:20:39,745 --> 00:20:42,425
Perfect, then. Let's meet this evening.

226
00:20:43,505 --> 00:20:44,785
See you soon.

227
00:20:46,225 --> 00:20:48,745
Don't say I didn't warn you.

228
00:20:50,385 --> 00:20:51,425
What are you saying?

229
00:20:52,025 --> 00:20:54,065
I'm talking to the mosquitoes, not you.

230
00:20:54,145 --> 00:20:57,745
I warned you.
Don't bite me, or I'll swat you to death.

231
00:20:57,825 --> 00:20:59,745
What sane person would talk to a mosquito?

232
00:20:59,825 --> 00:21:01,505
You're getting crazier every day.

233
00:21:01,585 --> 00:21:02,825
I'd better go grocery shopping.

234
00:21:04,545 --> 00:21:07,905
Die! See? I told you not to bite me.

235
00:21:07,985 --> 00:21:10,785
Guess I can only stand up to mosquitoes.

236
00:21:12,945 --> 00:21:14,185
Eat up.

237
00:21:15,625 --> 00:21:18,585
You too. You should eat plenty.

238
00:21:18,665 --> 00:21:20,865
You've lost so much weight.
You know that, right?

239
00:21:22,905 --> 00:21:24,505
You're no different, Neen.

240
00:21:26,825 --> 00:21:27,985
You still love me, though?

241
00:21:29,825 --> 00:21:31,425
Of course I do.

242
00:21:32,345 --> 00:21:35,465
I love you more and more every day.

243
00:21:47,065 --> 00:21:48,105
Yes, Mom?

244
00:21:50,985 --> 00:21:52,185
What did you say?

245
00:21:52,785 --> 00:21:54,385
You're not feeling well?

246
00:22:00,385 --> 00:22:02,705
Sure. I'll be right over.

247
00:22:02,785 --> 00:22:04,105
Okay.

248
00:22:08,745 --> 00:22:10,865
-Neen--
-Get the check.

249
00:22:11,385 --> 00:22:12,745
I'll come with you.

250
00:22:19,225 --> 00:22:21,785
Runch is on her way. Please wait for her.

251
00:22:24,345 --> 00:22:26,025
I don't think

252
00:22:26,105 --> 00:22:28,825
I can stay for dinner today.

253
00:22:29,505 --> 00:22:30,905
What? Why not?

254
00:22:35,265 --> 00:22:37,665
Can I ask you something?

255
00:22:40,625 --> 00:22:42,385
Is Runch married?

256
00:22:47,945 --> 00:22:48,745
Yes.

257
00:22:50,665 --> 00:22:52,025
Please let me explain.

258
00:22:52,105 --> 00:22:54,305
Runch has been having problems
with her wife.

259
00:22:54,385 --> 00:22:55,625
They're about to break up.

260
00:22:55,705 --> 00:22:57,705
What? Why would you say that, honey?

261
00:22:57,785 --> 00:23:00,265
I'm just telling the truth.
Why should I hide it?

262
00:23:02,545 --> 00:23:05,145
I'm sorry I never told you about this.

263
00:23:05,225 --> 00:23:08,065
I figured they'd get divorced soon anyway,

264
00:23:08,145 --> 00:23:10,625
so I decided not to tell you about it.

265
00:23:10,705 --> 00:23:13,785
Did I hear something about a divorce, Mom?

266
00:23:18,665 --> 00:23:19,745
What are you doing here?

267
00:23:19,825 --> 00:23:21,825
How could you ask that? How rude!

268
00:23:21,905 --> 00:23:24,545
She's my close friend's daughter.

269
00:23:24,625 --> 00:23:26,705
She came here because I invited her,

270
00:23:26,785 --> 00:23:31,025
unlike you who's shameless enough
to come uninvited.

271
00:23:31,625 --> 00:23:35,425
Judging from your foul mouth,
looks like you faked being sick.

272
00:23:35,505 --> 00:23:36,585
You're so full of it.

273
00:23:37,305 --> 00:23:39,865
You punk! Are you saying
I bullshitted Runch?

274
00:23:39,945 --> 00:23:42,505
Good. So you're self-aware.
Now I won't have to say it.

275
00:23:42,585 --> 00:23:43,705
Stop it, Neen.

276
00:23:44,505 --> 00:23:46,905
Tell her to stop first, then I'll stop.

277
00:23:47,825 --> 00:23:50,305
Maylin, I'm so sorry

278
00:23:50,385 --> 00:23:52,745
for dragging you into this mess here.

279
00:23:52,825 --> 00:23:54,945
I think I'd better go.

280
00:23:55,025 --> 00:23:58,265
-Wait. You still haven't eaten.
-Next time, Aunt Ging.

281
00:23:58,945 --> 00:23:59,785
See you later.

282
00:23:59,865 --> 00:24:00,985
See you later.

283
00:24:01,065 --> 00:24:02,145
Maylin…

284
00:24:06,465 --> 00:24:08,945
You punk! You ruined everything!

285
00:24:09,025 --> 00:24:10,385
You're one to talk.

286
00:24:10,465 --> 00:24:13,305
What were you planning to do?
Why'd you invite her over?

287
00:24:13,385 --> 00:24:15,465
And you even told her
we're getting divorced.

288
00:24:15,545 --> 00:24:17,945
What are you doing?
Finding a side chick for your daughter?

289
00:24:18,025 --> 00:24:20,745
What side chick?
Don't you dare insult Maylin like that!

290
00:24:20,825 --> 00:24:22,745
I wasn't insulting her. It's the truth.

291
00:24:22,825 --> 00:24:24,705
She's messing with a married woman.

292
00:24:24,785 --> 00:24:28,065
What would she be
if not a side chick? A mistress?

293
00:24:28,705 --> 00:24:30,545
You crazy bitch!

294
00:24:31,265 --> 00:24:34,465
Runch, let's go home. We need to talk.

295
00:24:35,625 --> 00:24:39,425
Runch. Runch, don't go!

296
00:24:39,505 --> 00:24:41,865
-Runch, wait.
-Honey.

297
00:24:41,945 --> 00:24:43,705
Runch! Runch!

298
00:24:47,385 --> 00:24:48,625
Honey…

299
00:24:56,225 --> 00:24:57,825
I admit it's all my fault

300
00:24:57,905 --> 00:25:00,785
for not telling you
Mom introduced me to Maylin.

301
00:25:00,865 --> 00:25:02,585
So you do know it's your fault.

302
00:25:03,625 --> 00:25:05,385
I already asked you

303
00:25:05,465 --> 00:25:09,345
if you were hiding something from me.
And you said no.

304
00:25:09,425 --> 00:25:11,345
You even promised me.

305
00:25:11,425 --> 00:25:13,745
It's barely been a day, Runch.

306
00:25:16,705 --> 00:25:18,825
I have no excuse.

307
00:25:21,705 --> 00:25:24,065
But the reason I didn't tell you

308
00:25:24,145 --> 00:25:26,545
is because I didn't want you to worry.

309
00:25:26,625 --> 00:25:28,705
And I don't have feelings for her.

310
00:25:28,785 --> 00:25:30,225
But she does.

311
00:25:31,825 --> 00:25:35,745
She knows I'm married,
so she probably doesn't.

312
00:25:37,225 --> 00:25:40,665
So what? Your mom takes her side,

313
00:25:40,745 --> 00:25:42,305
so of course she'd want you.

314
00:25:42,385 --> 00:25:44,345
My mom wouldn't do anything like that.

315
00:25:44,425 --> 00:25:45,705
She'd do way worse.

316
00:25:47,265 --> 00:25:49,025
Your mom told that girl

317
00:25:49,105 --> 00:25:51,425
we're getting divorced, even when…

318
00:25:57,305 --> 00:25:59,705
Well, we are getting divorced for real.

319
00:26:01,625 --> 00:26:03,385
But your mom doesn't know that.

320
00:26:03,465 --> 00:26:06,905
That means your mom lied to that girl

321
00:26:06,985 --> 00:26:09,705
because she wanted her
to replace me as your wife so bad.

322
00:26:09,785 --> 00:26:12,105
No one could ever replace you, Neen.

323
00:26:25,545 --> 00:26:27,585
And I'll never love anyone else.

324
00:26:31,025 --> 00:26:32,545
I only did what I did

325
00:26:33,065 --> 00:26:35,665
because I was trying to protect you.

326
00:26:36,625 --> 00:26:39,825
This isn't what lovers do
to protect each other.

327
00:26:41,185 --> 00:26:42,905
So what should I do then?

328
00:26:43,585 --> 00:26:47,385
What should I do for you to believe
that I really want to protect you?

329
00:26:48,585 --> 00:26:49,705
I don't know.

330
00:26:51,425 --> 00:26:53,465
I guess you'll have to prove it to me.

331
00:26:56,985 --> 00:26:58,825
Let's sleep in separate rooms tonight.

332
00:27:01,345 --> 00:27:02,385
Neen!

333
00:27:13,585 --> 00:27:16,065
Here's your breakfast
with a crispy fried egg.

334
00:28:03,385 --> 00:28:05,065
Maylin won't answer my calls.

335
00:28:05,145 --> 00:28:08,105
She won't read any of my texts either.
She must be mad at me.

336
00:28:11,265 --> 00:28:13,385
Did you hear what I said?

337
00:28:13,465 --> 00:28:15,425
What, honey? I'm watching the news.

338
00:28:15,505 --> 00:28:17,305
You never listen to me.

339
00:28:17,385 --> 00:28:20,585
I was. I heard you. I'm not deaf.

340
00:28:20,665 --> 00:28:23,625
I'm just tired of talking.
You wouldn't believe me anyway.

341
00:28:24,505 --> 00:28:26,865
What is it? Go ahead and speak.

342
00:28:26,945 --> 00:28:29,505
Why can't you stay out
of our daughter's life?

343
00:28:30,065 --> 00:28:31,225
Take it easy for once.

344
00:28:32,585 --> 00:28:35,705
Does Maylin know what you're trying to do?

345
00:28:37,025 --> 00:28:39,585
You're asking that
because you want to stop me, right?

346
00:28:39,665 --> 00:28:42,905
See? This is exactly why
I didn't want to talk!

347
00:28:42,985 --> 00:28:44,065
Wait.

348
00:28:44,745 --> 00:28:46,225
I didn't do anything wrong.

349
00:28:46,305 --> 00:28:47,585
I bet you see it too.

350
00:28:47,665 --> 00:28:50,905
Maylin is way sweeter and nicer
than our daughter-in-law.

351
00:28:50,985 --> 00:28:53,505
Don't you want
a daughter-in-law like that?

352
00:28:53,585 --> 00:28:55,385
Are you nuts?

353
00:28:56,745 --> 00:28:58,905
Runch is married to Neen.

354
00:28:58,985 --> 00:29:01,985
They have a marriage certificate too.
Why are you doing this?

355
00:29:02,065 --> 00:29:03,305
Marriages can end in divorce.

356
00:29:03,945 --> 00:29:06,065
Soon, they'll be fed up with this anyway.

357
00:29:06,145 --> 00:29:07,785
So this is why you're always

358
00:29:07,865 --> 00:29:09,185
messing with her.

359
00:29:09,265 --> 00:29:11,625
I can't believe you're so competitive

360
00:29:11,705 --> 00:29:15,345
you won't even care
about our daughter's feelings.

361
00:29:15,425 --> 00:29:17,665
Divorcing that rich kid
can only be good for us.

362
00:29:17,745 --> 00:29:20,985
Trust me, the moment Runch divorces her
and marries someone else,

363
00:29:21,065 --> 00:29:22,785
she'll have a better life for sure.

364
00:29:24,305 --> 00:29:26,345
Who will? Her or you?

365
00:29:26,425 --> 00:29:28,305
Everything I do is for my daughter, Pong.

366
00:29:28,385 --> 00:29:32,025
Can't you see how inferior
our daughter is to her wife?

367
00:29:33,345 --> 00:29:35,465
I want people to admire Runch

368
00:29:35,545 --> 00:29:39,225
for achieving success on her own,
not because of someone else.

369
00:29:40,625 --> 00:29:42,345
If she can't handle the fact

370
00:29:42,425 --> 00:29:45,345
or can't accept it,
she has to decide for herself.

371
00:29:45,425 --> 00:29:46,985
Why are you deciding for her?

372
00:29:48,345 --> 00:29:50,465
I don't want to see my daughter
being humbled.

373
00:29:50,985 --> 00:29:53,625
Plus, I hate that brat.

374
00:29:55,705 --> 00:29:57,585
I've always warned you, Ging.

375
00:29:57,665 --> 00:30:01,305
Runch doesn't talk much.
She just tolerates everything.

376
00:30:01,825 --> 00:30:05,705
But if one day she can't
take it anymore, I guarantee you

377
00:30:06,345 --> 00:30:07,785
she'll run away so far

378
00:30:07,865 --> 00:30:09,985
that you won't get to see her again.

379
00:30:10,065 --> 00:30:11,105
No way.

380
00:30:11,625 --> 00:30:15,065
I raised Runch. I know what she's like.

381
00:30:16,265 --> 00:30:19,825
One day you'll regret
doing this to her family.

382
00:30:33,225 --> 00:30:34,945
What are you looking at, honey?

383
00:30:35,025 --> 00:30:36,545
It's this.

384
00:30:36,625 --> 00:30:39,025
The photo of Neen and Runch. Look!

385
00:30:39,105 --> 00:30:42,265
After their trip to the country house,
they've been together every day.

386
00:30:42,345 --> 00:30:45,025
And they've been
posting pictures every day.

387
00:30:45,105 --> 00:30:48,505
Seeing this makes me super happy.

388
00:30:49,545 --> 00:30:50,625
Look.

389
00:30:50,705 --> 00:30:53,825
Neen, why didn't you tell me you'd come?

390
00:30:55,985 --> 00:30:58,665
You came alone? What about Runch?

391
00:31:00,185 --> 00:31:02,305
-I don't know.
-What?

392
00:31:05,265 --> 00:31:06,625
Why are you fighting this time?

393
00:31:07,665 --> 00:31:09,185
Just now, Mom was so happy

394
00:31:09,265 --> 00:31:12,025
to see you head over heels in love
with your wife.

395
00:31:12,705 --> 00:31:15,465
Can you not mention it?
I'm so fed up with it.

396
00:31:16,065 --> 00:31:17,065
Did you have a fight?

397
00:31:17,585 --> 00:31:20,025
Then what do I do now?

398
00:31:20,105 --> 00:31:21,705
What do you mean?

399
00:31:23,305 --> 00:31:27,185
Did you really forget? Seriously?

400
00:31:31,785 --> 00:31:33,465
Oh no!

401
00:31:33,545 --> 00:31:35,225
I completely forgot.

402
00:31:36,865 --> 00:31:39,665
What do we do now?

403
00:31:52,905 --> 00:31:54,865
What's up, Neen?

404
00:32:02,985 --> 00:32:05,305
I just came to tell you to meet me

405
00:32:05,385 --> 00:32:07,225
in the fitting room tomorrow at 3 p.m.

406
00:32:07,305 --> 00:32:10,145
because there'll be
an office party at night.

407
00:32:10,225 --> 00:32:11,345
That's all.

408
00:32:15,425 --> 00:32:17,265
Hang on.

409
00:32:19,665 --> 00:32:22,065
Won't you sit down and talk first?

410
00:32:24,785 --> 00:32:25,945
No, thanks.

411
00:32:57,945 --> 00:33:02,225
I'm being this seductive,
yet she won't even budge?

412
00:33:49,065 --> 00:33:51,985
SHOP, EAT, USE OUR SERVICES
YOU CAN EARN M POINTS

413
00:34:01,665 --> 00:34:02,785
Hello, ma'am.

414
00:34:02,865 --> 00:34:04,265
Hello.

415
00:34:14,344 --> 00:34:15,985
-This one, please.
-Sure.

416
00:34:16,065 --> 00:34:17,344
This way, please.

417
00:34:26,145 --> 00:34:27,425
Can I earn M points here?

418
00:34:27,505 --> 00:34:29,225
Yes, you can earn your M points.

419
00:34:29,304 --> 00:34:32,744
May I have the phone number
registered to your M card?

420
00:34:32,824 --> 00:34:33,705
Sure.

421
00:34:34,385 --> 00:34:36,665
-Ms. Runchlaphat, correct?
-Yes.

422
00:34:36,744 --> 00:34:40,744
Would you like to redeem your M points
for an extra 12.5% off on top of that?

423
00:34:40,824 --> 00:34:42,025
You may do it here.

424
00:34:42,105 --> 00:34:43,985
-Sure.
-Okay.

425
00:34:45,665 --> 00:34:47,465
The original price was 5,600 baht.

426
00:34:47,545 --> 00:34:50,585
After the discount,
your total comes to 4,900 baht.

427
00:34:51,344 --> 00:34:52,465
That's quite a bargain.

428
00:34:52,545 --> 00:34:55,665
It sure is. Would you like
to add anything else, ma'am?

429
00:34:57,665 --> 00:34:58,745
No. I'm all set.

430
00:34:58,825 --> 00:35:00,785
Okay. One moment, please.

431
00:35:01,385 --> 00:35:02,345
How would you like to pay?

432
00:35:02,425 --> 00:35:04,905
-QR code, please.
-QR? Okay.

433
00:35:09,025 --> 00:35:11,585
You look good in everything, Ms. Runch.

434
00:35:11,665 --> 00:35:12,945
Thank you.

435
00:35:18,785 --> 00:35:20,585
Ms. Peeracha is done.

436
00:35:31,385 --> 00:35:34,185
Neen, isn't this dress…

437
00:35:34,265 --> 00:35:35,705
It's pretty, right?

438
00:35:38,825 --> 00:35:40,785
It is, but…

439
00:35:42,025 --> 00:35:43,865
it's backless.

440
00:35:45,185 --> 00:35:47,065
It sure is. It's intentional.

441
00:35:48,505 --> 00:35:51,705
You're the one who said
I'd look good in anything.

442
00:35:51,785 --> 00:35:54,145
So this dress
should make me look good too.

443
00:35:59,265 --> 00:36:02,385
I meant something more modest.

444
00:36:02,905 --> 00:36:06,625
If you wear this to the party,
all eyes will be on you.

445
00:36:06,705 --> 00:36:09,985
Oh? So you'd get jealous if people looked?

446
00:36:12,105 --> 00:36:14,905
Neen, please don't play games with me.

447
00:36:17,385 --> 00:36:19,465
Excuse me. I'd like to buy this dress.

448
00:36:19,545 --> 00:36:20,425
Sure.

449
00:36:22,625 --> 00:36:24,225
Neen.

450
00:36:33,865 --> 00:36:37,425
Why aren't Neen and Runch here yet?

451
00:36:41,665 --> 00:36:42,505
There they are.

452
00:36:50,145 --> 00:36:51,905
Why are you so late, honey?

453
00:36:51,985 --> 00:36:53,865
We were stuck in traffic, Mom.

454
00:36:55,865 --> 00:36:56,785
Hey, Neen.

455
00:37:01,265 --> 00:37:02,345
-Whoa.
-What?

456
00:37:02,425 --> 00:37:04,745
Isn't the dress a little too pretty?

457
00:37:04,825 --> 00:37:07,665
It's nothing unusual, Nai. It's fabulous.

458
00:37:09,905 --> 00:37:11,465
Don't squeeze me so hard.

459
00:37:11,985 --> 00:37:15,825
Oh, sorry. I was just…

460
00:37:26,425 --> 00:37:27,425
Jealous?

461
00:37:32,065 --> 00:37:34,225
Excuse me? Did you forget

462
00:37:34,305 --> 00:37:35,825
it's not just the two of you?

463
00:37:38,665 --> 00:37:41,425
Come on. Let's go
sit at our table, shall we?

464
00:37:41,505 --> 00:37:42,345
Sure.

465
00:37:42,865 --> 00:37:44,465
-Let's go.
-That way.

466
00:37:44,545 --> 00:37:45,465
This way.

467
00:37:51,345 --> 00:37:52,865
Isn't that dress a little too much?

468
00:38:05,145 --> 00:38:07,505
My hip…

469
00:38:09,505 --> 00:38:10,665
My hip!

470
00:38:18,745 --> 00:38:21,745
Pong isn't home either.

471
00:38:23,265 --> 00:38:24,745
What do I do?

472
00:38:31,705 --> 00:38:34,145
MOM

473
00:38:40,385 --> 00:38:42,025
She's probably sick again.

474
00:38:49,745 --> 00:38:51,945
Why won't you pick up, Runch?

475
00:38:55,625 --> 00:38:57,025
Neen, honey,

476
00:38:57,745 --> 00:38:59,945
will you dance with me?

477
00:39:57,905 --> 00:40:00,065
Are you still mad at me?

478
00:40:00,705 --> 00:40:01,705
Yeah.

479
00:40:03,625 --> 00:40:05,625
When will you forgive me?

480
00:40:07,825 --> 00:40:10,625
I don't know.
I'll have to see how you behave.

481
00:40:13,025 --> 00:40:16,625
Looks like you won't forgive me
so easily this time.

482
00:40:20,505 --> 00:40:22,145
Every couple

483
00:40:22,225 --> 00:40:24,945
is bound to have misunderstandings.

484
00:40:25,865 --> 00:40:27,905
But what matters is

485
00:40:28,625 --> 00:40:31,065
whether we still hold each other's hands.

486
00:40:36,265 --> 00:40:38,305
I need to use the restroom.

487
00:40:40,865 --> 00:40:42,025
I'll wait at the table.

488
00:41:10,585 --> 00:41:12,425
MAYLINYA

489
00:41:16,345 --> 00:41:17,305
Hello?

490
00:41:19,225 --> 00:41:20,305
What?

491
00:41:20,985 --> 00:41:22,505
Mom fell in the bathroom?

492
00:41:24,785 --> 00:41:26,945
Mom, how are you doing?

493
00:41:28,705 --> 00:41:30,185
Does it hurt a lot?

494
00:41:31,705 --> 00:41:34,505
Of course it does.
It hurt so bad I couldn't get up.

495
00:41:34,585 --> 00:41:36,505
I could've died in front of the bathroom.

496
00:41:36,585 --> 00:41:39,025
You wouldn't pick up,
no matter how many times I called.

497
00:41:40,225 --> 00:41:43,745
You were so busy at the party
that you ignored me.

498
00:41:43,825 --> 00:41:46,585
Luckily, Maylin came and helped me.

499
00:41:47,105 --> 00:41:49,705
Otherwise, I would've died.

500
00:41:49,785 --> 00:41:51,905
It wasn't that bad a fall.
You couldn't have died.

501
00:41:51,985 --> 00:41:54,825
Who's talking to you?
I'm talking to my daughter.

502
00:41:55,705 --> 00:41:57,305
If my daughter-in-law was someone else,

503
00:41:57,945 --> 00:42:00,585
my daughter would've picked up
and come straight home.

504
00:42:00,665 --> 00:42:03,545
It's because of you
that Runch is rebelling against me.

505
00:42:03,625 --> 00:42:05,105
-What? But--
-Neen!

506
00:42:05,625 --> 00:42:06,665
Enough.

507
00:42:16,065 --> 00:42:17,145
Mom.

508
00:42:19,185 --> 00:42:20,625
With what happened today,

509
00:42:21,265 --> 00:42:22,745
I'm very upset.

510
00:42:24,465 --> 00:42:27,825
But what you just said
is totally unfair to Neen.

511
00:42:33,105 --> 00:42:35,745
You have no right
to set me up with someone else.

512
00:42:41,025 --> 00:42:44,185
You have no right to replace Neen
with someone else.

513
00:42:44,985 --> 00:42:47,905
And you have no right
to make her feel less than.

514
00:42:47,985 --> 00:42:51,505
So you'd speak up for her

515
00:42:52,025 --> 00:42:53,665
rather than your mom?

516
00:42:53,745 --> 00:42:55,105
Yes, Mom.

517
00:43:08,785 --> 00:43:10,385
I married her.

518
00:43:10,985 --> 00:43:13,425
She is my family.

519
00:43:15,585 --> 00:43:18,425
You have to respect my decision.

520
00:43:29,785 --> 00:43:30,905
Mom.

521
00:43:33,225 --> 00:43:36,465
I won't let anyone
hurt my wife's feelings.

522
00:43:37,465 --> 00:43:39,025
No one.

523
00:43:39,825 --> 00:43:41,305
Not even you, Mom.

524
00:43:50,265 --> 00:43:51,705
Let's go home.

525
00:44:54,065 --> 00:44:55,625
Are you mad at the rain?

526
00:44:58,345 --> 00:45:00,625
There goes my plan
for a romantic beach trip.

527
00:45:00,705 --> 00:45:02,425
My first date with a gorgeous girl.

528
00:45:04,305 --> 00:45:06,705
I'm mad at everything right now.

529
00:45:06,785 --> 00:45:11,225
You're cute even when you're mad.

530
00:45:13,465 --> 00:45:15,105
If the rain doesn't stop,

531
00:45:15,625 --> 00:45:18,225
should we stay in our room
all day and all night?

532
00:45:23,225 --> 00:45:24,785
What would we do

533
00:45:24,865 --> 00:45:27,145
if we stayed here all day and all night?

534
00:45:32,865 --> 00:45:36,425
Whatever shall we do…?

535
00:45:38,305 --> 00:45:39,345
Hey.

536
00:45:45,025 --> 00:45:46,425
I have an idea

537
00:45:47,105 --> 00:45:49,065
of what we should do.

538
00:45:50,105 --> 00:45:52,305
I guarantee you won't get bored.

539
00:45:52,385 --> 00:45:54,025
What are you doing, Runch?

540
00:45:58,705 --> 00:46:01,385
Runch! Don't do that.

541
00:46:01,905 --> 00:46:03,665
We won't be able to stop.

542
00:46:09,105 --> 00:46:10,585
Can we never stop, then?

543
00:46:22,545 --> 00:46:24,105
I love you, Runch.

544
00:46:26,585 --> 00:46:28,345
I love you too, Neen.

545
00:46:36,185 --> 00:46:38,745
I want you to break up with that brat.

546
00:46:38,825 --> 00:46:40,105
If I had known

547
00:46:40,625 --> 00:46:42,825
that you'd be like this
after marrying her,

548
00:46:43,345 --> 00:46:44,945
I would've done everything to stop you!

549
00:46:45,025 --> 00:46:47,825
I love Neen. We love each other.

550
00:46:47,905 --> 00:46:48,905
But I hate her!

551
00:46:48,985 --> 00:46:51,385
I hope this was the last time.

552
00:46:51,985 --> 00:46:53,785
I really want us to be happy together.

553
00:46:53,865 --> 00:46:56,265
I want us to be happy together too.

554
00:47:44,265 --> 00:47:46,265
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

